	</Content>
	<Content>
		<div class='text-width'>
			<h2>Bringing clarity to aircraft maneuver grades</h2>
			<p>
				Instead of assigning mixed grades for each maneuver performed, grades were passed down 
				to each parameter inside of a maneuver. This gives pilots a more complete view of the 
				flight characteristics from when each maneuver was performed. The intent to prioritize 
				the findability of page content gives pilots a streamlined way to process information.
			</p>
		</div>
		<img
			src='/content/case-studies/dod/left-sidebar.png'
			class='view-project-image content'
		/>
	</Content>
	<Content>
		<div class='text-width'>
			<h2>Visualizing aircraft performance in real time</h2>
			<p>
				Timeline reel now displays numerical timestamps and vertical dividers in a layered yet 
				compact format. Comments and maneuver markers are embedded within the timeline reel that 
				spatially orients events at specific moments of time. This change alone brings a fresh perspective 
				for pilots to see when and what activity has occurred in the file at a high-level.
			</p>
			<p>
				Realtime information of the aircraft's performance is now displayed to pilots in a visually 
				engaging format. While the addition of parameters gives pilots an extra level of information 
				awareness, it also opens the opportunity for human intervention to manually inspect the 
				performance of maneuvers graded by artificial intelligence.
			</p>
		</div>
		<img
			src='/content/case-studies/dod/timeline.png'
			class='view-project-image content'
		/>
	</Content>
	<Content>
		<div class='text-width'>
			<h2>Results</h2>
			<p>
				The redesign of DDR saw significant improvements across the customer journey by reducing points of friction, 
				resulting in an increase in engagement and user satisfaction. The final design solution successfully met our 
				user and business goals by establishing a seamless experience that encourages autonomy and self-improvement 
				as a pilot.
			</p>
			<p>
				Some of the noticeable improvements our team observed are:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<b>Increased average session duration:</b> Feature engagement improved by 40% as users spent more time 
					interacting with the product
				</li>
				<li>
					<b>Improved workflow speed:</b> The task completion rate for primary tasks (upload file, add note) 
					improved by 15%
				</li>
				<li>
					<b>Happier customers:</b> Post-launch interviews revealed an increase in user satisfaction with using 
					the web application
				</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Pilots reported feeling more confident in their decisions and less frustrated by the application, 
				adding comments such as “The new design is much more intuitive and easier to use” and “This is a 
				serious upgrade compared to what was available before”.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class='text-width'>
			<blockquote>
				"“Hiring Chris brought us instant relaxation. Having someone dedicated to solving usability and design problems 
				freed up other team members to do their jobs. Before working with Chris I didn’t realize how much it would take to 
				do the research sitting down with pilots to better solve their problems.”
			</blockquote>
			<div>
				<p><b>Julian Capps</b></p>
				<p>Head of Defense, Crowdbotics</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</Content>
